runs.comm: starts back of a length, takes Warner's pad and bobbles down by his feet
touch fuller outside off, pushed into the covers
very full, going for the yorker, turned away backward of square and short fine-leg comes around
full on off stump, Watson always likes to get forward and does so here with a controlled outside edge to third man
dropped in short, Warner goes for the pull and, although he doesn't middle it, there's plenty of power as it goes wide of mid-on and runs away
back of a length outside off, driven firmly off the back foot to cover
on off stump, comes forward and pushes into the leg side
good length on middle and off, defended towards mid-off
well bowled! This zips off the pitch outside off stump and Warner feels for it away from his body as he gets beaten
full on leg stump, shapes into Warner and takes the pad to the leg side
full on the stumps, Watson gets forward and plays across his front pad towards midwicket
tight on middle and off, defended to the covers...quiet start from the openers
deflected away fine, angled into Watson and it takes a thick inside through fine leg and it speeds over the outfield
back on off stump, short of a length and defended at the top of the bounce to cover
loses his line down the leg side, Wilson does well to get a glove on it
again, poor ball, fired down the leg side by Rankin
close! Aims to play this through the leg side and gets a big leading edge that loops over mid-on...that's the use of today's very big bat edges!
full outside off, defended firmly into the covers
short ball going down the leg side, Watson doesn't connect with his pull and that's another extra
and another, this is pretty poor from Rankin as another one is speared past the pads
that's more like it, back of a length on off stump and it climbs at Watson taking the handle down to third man
outside off stump, Warner fetches it into the leg side and will keep the strike at the end of a long over
powerful drive, Warner offered a touch of width and he unleashes through the line of the ball
pushed firmly into the off side between cover and mid-off
dragged down short and that's easy for Watson as he pulls it strongly backward of square...sat up nicely off the surface
width outside off this time, Watson just stands there and drives dismissively through the off side...power and placement
slower ball on off stump, defended carefully back towards the bowler
poor line again, on leg stump and flicked effortlessly over deep square-leg...didn't use brute force there, just timing
starts down the leg side with a wide, Wilson takes it neatly and whips off the bails
outside leg stump, the bowler is fortunate that this takes the pad into the leg side
full outside off, driven into the off side
full on middle and off, pushed towards midwicket
very full outside off, a booming drive from Watson although not quite timed and mid-off dives to his right to cut it off
nicely timed off the back foot, pinged it to cover who dives and gets his left hand on it but can only parry the ball away
short ball outside off, comes back a touch into Watson and he deflects it to short third man
what a classy shot by Warner, was a full ball on off stump and he places it between cover and mid-off with outstanding timing
he's round the wicket, full on the stumps and work down to mid-on
pushed in towards leg stump, takes the pad to the on side
touch slower, on middle and off, hint of turn and defended to off side
plays this late off the stumps, chopped down to short third-man
a touch short outside off stump, cut away off the back foot and pulls up just short of the deep cover boundary
on leg stump, flicked to midwicket
back of a length, pushed across Warner, driven off the back foot down the ground
hint of shape into Watson who plays it late down to third man
poor delivery, outside leg stump and another superb piece of timing as he flicks it backward of square through the leg side
played into the off side
full outside off, driven without much timing down to long-off
that's the breakthrough...Warner used his feet and flicked it sweetly into the leg side but straight to the man at deep midwicket
touch shorter, played square through the off side through the covers
full on middle stump, worked down the ground to long-on
nicely bowled, tossed up on middle and off, comes forward and gets a thick inside edge
well bowled...slides across the left hander and beats the outside edge. Wilson appeals for a stumping but Hussey got his foot back
opens the face into the off side
hint of width outside off, driven through the covers
round the wicket, swung from outside off straight to midwicket
dropped driven straight down the pitch and Stirling can't hold on as he struck up his left hand
full on the stumps, flicked along the ground and beats a diving midwicket
nicely played, short on leg stump and Watson sweeps it firmly backward of square
now he drops short and gets pulled over the deep midwicket boundary...Watson following his wickets with a very solid innings
an appeal for lbw as Hussey misses a sweep but it pitched outside leg...would have been out if Porterfield had it
angled to backward point and that would have been close with a direct hit
that's Watson brutal power, dragged down short and he flat-bats it straight down the ground to beat long-on...he's in a rush
that's massive! Watson deep in his crease again and pulls it high and handsome over deep midwicket to take him to a 28-ball fifty
gets this one fuller and it's driven down the ground
wrong line outside leg stump, Hussey paddles it in a very controlled fashion behind square on the on side
on off stump, opens the face to short third-man who makes a direct hit and Watson is caught short by Johnston's throw. That was a bit lazy from him
worked neatly off the stumps through short fine-leg
pushed firmly towards mid-off and Hussey is quick between the wickets
on off stump, defended with bat and pad together
tucked off the stumps through the leg side
gone! The umpire decides that was pad first. Shaped back late into Hussey who was pushing forward and got caught in front of middle and off
starts with a short ball, White pulls in front of square through midwicket and they make a third with some good running...ah, but wait, it was called one short
short of a length on off stump, worked into the leg side
cut away into the off side, they race off for the run and the fielder fumbles when a clean pick-up would have provided a run-out chance
banged in very short outside off stump, climbs through to the keeper and that's a wide
back full on off stump, defended to the on side
dropped, but that would have been a blinder from Johnston. He was pulled off the top of the bat towards mid-on where Johnston leapt to his right and couldn't grab the rebound
mistimes another pull as he gets a bottom edge into his leg which bobbles to the off side
full on off stump, pushed up to mid-off
full on the stumps, whipped firmly out to midwicket
on the pads, worked away out to deep square
goes for the pull, but it is another unconvincing effort as he plays over the delivery
dragged wide outside off, White drills it with a lot of power off the back foot but straight to deep cover
opens the face and finds short third-man
back of a length on off stump, defended into the off side
angled into the pads, deflected into the leg side
chopped away into the off side, struggling for his timing here as he finds backward point
another short ball, this time he pulls and gets it in front of square
fuller delivery, White hanging on the back foot and gets more of an inside edge down to long leg
that's better, another short ball. Gets his timing and placement this time as he pulls backward of square and finds the gap
that's pretty dismissive from White as he picks up a fractionally short delivery outside off and cracks it away through midwicket
pushes this fuller and it's driven to mid-off
this is hurry to a finish now, dropped in short at gentle pace and he swivels onto a pull sending it fine of long leg
slower ball full on middle, punched nearly down the ground for brace
driven off the back foot through the covers
swing and a miss. Scoots past off stump, a coat of varnish job. He lifted his head on the shot.
that's the game, lofted comfortably over the leg side out to the deep midwicket boundary
